column494: survey_post.1.player.survey_strategy_free_text
By maximising Allshire rewards I was maximising my own.
my strategy was to meet allshire targets
I wanted to make sure that I was always maximising my gains. If we weren't and someone else was taking coins for themselves then I would invest to make sure we hit the target.

Decided on a strategy i.e. always invest the same way for everyones benefit and didn't change my feelings about the 'others' although felt vindicated in the strategy given % payoff. I realise I could have had more tokens personally but potentially at cost (and trust) of others.
it was an interesting game, picking a winning strategy was reasonably easy

I feel that the two groups do not have much importance and only Allshire and the individual has significance. The strategy I used was to invest in Allshire most of the time in the hopes that other people would do the same and then occasionally gamble with not investing.
I thought there was a good chance 4 people would go for Allshire so I decided to take that chance as it had a higher payout.
i started off investing but as another player wasnt i thought why should i?
It was interesting to see how many people would keep the coin.
Once i saw everyone else was investing i decide to invest in every round

on the whole I did the best for allshire to try and get us all 2 coins. I gambled a few times to keep the coin, sometimes it paid off, sometimes it didn't. Majority of times I chose allshire to get 2 coins.
It went the way I wanted it to with everyone acting in the best interest of the group. It was great that nobody tried to keep their coin.
I tried to share as best I thought.

When the whole group goal was investing in Allshire it made it easier to decide to work as a group. When coins were kept for individuals it made it more difficult to trust that everyone was working to the same goal.
I felt disheartened when people chose to keep the coin,we would all be better off investing the coin.
I felt that the risk of selecting the extra coin option did not outweigh the reward of guaranteeing +2 on every go so i went all in to Allshire each time
I wanted to make sure we all got our fair share
I felt it would bring about the fairest outcome if we all voted to get 2 coins, nobody loses.

I realised that most people were voting to invest in Allshire because they noticed that they'd have the best chance at maximising their earnings that way . People are innately selfish and if me and the other player hadn't taken the opportunity most of the time to keep the coin , they would have taken that opportunity for themselves
it took a long time
I wanted to maximise coins for the whole
Thew game was straightforward and in most rounds everybody invested
I was playing along with the rest but was going to go on my own near the end
The others frequently met the threshold for the payout, so maximised my earnings.
I was trying to predict what the other players were going to do to maximise my winnings.
use keep coin sparingly when overall morale is down
I wanted the team to share the same outcome

I was pleased that all 6 people continued to invest in Allshire each time, I think it showed solidarity and community. I didn't have a strategy, I chose to always invest in the group and was happy to do this without trying to maximise earnings.
It annoyed me that the others seemed to be game playing and selfish. The greater good was preferable to getting a little extra individually
I decided I would always invest the coin unless a point came when the group were not making the target.
I wanted the maximum gain for myself and the other players
I just wanted the best outcome for everyone so chose Allshire everytime
I felt that everyone for the most part in Westville wanted a good outcome and invested in the area.
I was trying to strike a a balance between earning enough for myself and still making sure that Allshire earned so varied my choices between keeping the coin or sharing it.

After a lot of people chose all shire, it always seemed likely that less than 4 people would choose all shire the next round since people clearly thought, oh it might be ok for me to choose myself and all shire might still win. except that was rare.
I didnt want it to drop below four so would only risk keeping it if i thought 4 would still give to allshire

I looked at the trend graph, which ever seemed on a declined would seem to bounce a little bit back on the next round. So when I feel that the Allshire investment was peaking too much I'd keep the coin in the next round.
I mostly went with allshire as I didn't want others to start keeping the coin ut with an occasional coin keep to increase my winnings
I was trying to guess what other players would choose to do
When I saw the majority of players investing in Allshire it made me feel a sense of community to Allshire and allowed me to justify placing my investments in Allshire in most rounds.
I noticed most people were picking Allshire, so then I chose to keep the coin in order to maximise the amount of coins I got. I also chose Allshire sometimes because I felt bed keeping the coin.
just went with my gut feeling

i did start with the thought of investing most times, but it soon became apparent that the investment targets were not going to be met, so i started keeping my coin.  saddening, but not unexpected.   an interesting game which illuminates the human condition.
I always played to invest in Allshire so everyone could win.
I have nothing more to add
Either be completely selfish or completely cooperative.
I felt that positive selections at the outset should indicate the optimum path for the group but that was undermined.
I did try to invest but ultimately with at least two other people consistently keeping their coin it was more of a risk to invest than keep it to myself.
I found it fun

It was disappointing to see peoples unwillingness to contribute as a whole, in the beginning this was my strategy however it became clear people were keeping the coins for themselves leaving me at a disadvantage
I thought everyone would always choose to invest in Allshire as it seemed the better outcome for every player, but I changed strategy when I realised this was not the case.
i was trying to guess what other people would do
I spent a long time waiting for others to play.
Trying to take turns in getting the extra coin by being one of the two that could was difficult - not numbered etc and could only see the total who voted not who.
I wanted to see if I could change the dynamic of the voting so feel like I was one of the first people to turn on Allshire and start keeping my coins so I could maximise my bonus.
I was generaly investing in allshire, with occasional coin retentions based on previous rounds investment
If everyone was trying to meet the target then i would keep the coin but it got a point whee everyone was keeping the coin so my decision was made for me

To begin with others were also being team players and we were all benefiting. Then people started to keeo their coins so i was getting zero coins. I let this happen a couple of times each round to see if people started to work as a team and invest too but when they didn't i kept the coin too as otherwise i was getting nothing by trying to work with others and they were benefitting
I felt disappointed that other people chose to keep the coins to maximise their own reward
I wanted to get 3 points as much as possible, gain their trust so that enough would invest and then I would keep the coin.
Kind of randomised my choices sometimes. Hoping the group would choose the same things to share the wealth
i assumed everyone would choose the first option to insure everyone gets something
It made more sense to me to always invest in Allshire so everyone got 2 coins each time.I was annoyed that other people didn't do this.

I really wanted to stick with helping Allshire, but it became obvious that there were a few selfish people happy to pocket 3 each time, and it got harder as a team player to get any coins, so eventually I got frustrated and started acting selfishly too.
At the start I wanted to do the best for the team but slowly people chose selfishly, so I followed suit as otherwise the target would not have been met and I'd get no bonus.

I did consider switching to meet the target at one point, in order for the other participants to keep their coins and maximise, but there was no way to guarantee the others would do the same. I therefore decided to keep all my coins and guarantee I would get at least one coin each round.
When it felt like every body was being selfish I acted selfish to minimise loss

My plan at the beginning was to choose Allshire thinking that is what everyone else would do and we'd all maximise our winnings.  I quickly realised that this strategy wouldn't work as we were not going to meet the target.  After that I kept the coin on every round.
I just wanted Allshire to meet the target so I chose that option everytime. I think it is only fair to work in a group and a team to maximise the benefits.
My group - by and large - seemed to 'agree' that investing in Allshire would yield the best results for everybody. I agreed so did that every time
I felt that after one round when the players meet the target, the following round the players wanted to keep the coin to itself so i played accordingly
I wish I had started with allshire like the other 3 players,  the first two rounds there was opportunity to form a union and double our bonus.
none
I felt frustrated that I could not communicate and let others know we could work together
The game was interesting. I was focusing on meeting the target while maximising my own winnings at the same time. I felt the other players were sharing the same goal.
i felt a little bad if i took the coin but 5 others didn't, If one other took the coin felt vindicated and if only 4 invested i worried so went back to investing.
I just chose the invest in all option everytime in the hope everyone did to maximise everyones earnings.
I knew the other players were usally going to meet the target, so I would keep the coin to maximise my earnings
Towards the end of the game, the last 10 or so rounds, I persevered with investing in Allshire, in an attempt to push the majority to do the same. It was not a successful strategy.
Nothing
I figured if we all invested then we'd all get 2 coins - so everyone should be less greedy. Alas!
I feel that people were out for themselves at times and focused on the group at other times.

Safety first to see what other people were doing.  Making sure we all got 2 coins.  There were enough people doing this so there were opportunities for grabbing an extra coin with just a little risk.  The biggest risk was when we were down to 4.   The natural reaction was to play safe in the next round except once towards the end when I though the majority would play safe I played to keep the coin and it worked.

I tried to encourage us all to gain 2 coins each round, as this was not apparent I then decided to collect the 1 coin. I then tried again to get us all the 2 coins. It was frustrating as we could have all helped each other to maximise our earning opportunity but then others must not have agreed to this approach.
I always wanted to ensure at least 2 points every round.
simply tried to maximise my winnings and not get distracted
At the start I did not really look too carefully at the graphs, but by the third go I was using them

I felt from playing the game that the needs of the few are far outweighed by the needs of the many. In other words, we all played as a group to get the best outcome not only for ourselves but as a group working together.     I enjoyed taking part in this study. Thank you and good luck with your research.
At first I was investing into Allshire, then I realised everyone was being selfish so I was also selfish.
i decided to invest for the 1st 3 rounds and if others did the same i would continue to invest, if the target was not met on 2 of the 3 first rounds i would have switched to keep the coin
I observed the group behaviour changing over time from helping the group to just helping themselves
felt excited during the game
I felt everyone gave up after round 2. Half the group kept the coin and as no one flipped to sharing we all kept the coin from then on leading to less for all.
I felt it was somewhat predictable.
Took the route most likely to increase my coins.
I wanted the entire group to do well and was encouraged not to keep the coin as no-one else was.

I enjoyed the game and was strategic in my investment aiming to get more coins as I knew that the more I kept my coins and four other players invested in Allshire the more coins I get. i was also strategic in not being too selfish in order to prevent earning just a coin.

I tended to alternate between investing in Allshire and keeping the coin, so that we would meet the threshold often enough to encourage people to invest rather than always keeping the coin, but sometimes keeping the coin to max out my earnings.

I wanted everyone to get coins but i thought that, if everyone else was investing, I could take the money and get the best of both worlds!    As the game went on it appeared that others began to do the same and, when it started to fall below four investors, everyone just began to take the money.
I tried to get as many points as possible but I also wanted to keep the group motivated by selecting the invest option when I saw that other people were keep the coins.
I think we all chose to invest which showed we wanted to develop Allshire.
I would rather earn 1 coin (and Allshire fail to meet the target) than earn 2 and have others earn 3 through their selfishness.
As a bit of a socialist, I wanted to work as a collective group and so opted to go for the option that would benefit everyone the most
I didn't believe there were other players involved. I suspected that I was being manipulated, so simply chose to consistently keep the coin.

I really wanted to opt for Allshire rather than keep coin as benefits me and the whole group.  I tried that but no one else seemed to be doing that so I would end with nothing so I ended up keeping the coins or would have ended with nothing
was going to invest until i saw most others keep coin themselves
I always chose to invest the coins in Allshire as if we all did we made the most money for the group as possible.
I tried to do it so we all got more but then when others stopped I didn't see the point in continuing like that. I tried again at the end but others did not
I wanted to keep the same decision all the way through the game to maximise my bonus
everyone seemed to play the game together, therefore maximizing our winnings
I wanted to trust the others so started the first round as invested in. When everybody else did the same and then was more than happy to keep doing this.
I wanted to help Allshire meet the target regardless of how many coins I got.

I put the coin in the first time to see how many would do the same.  We almost met the target so I figured I'd do it again in the hope that one more person would join in and help us reach the target, but they did not.  After that I kept it each time.  If the target had been met by the other players in one round, I would have put my coin in again to try to keep it going.    This felt like a real game with other players.  Most studies that say you'll be playing in a group are not being truthful.  So, well done for that!  Have a great day.

every time for the first go i tried to invest for the whole to benefit everyone more but no one else ever voted for this - always always they kept the coin so then I did too. Utterly depressing how selfish everyone appeared to be in this game and also ended up with less by being selfish

My plan was to retain my coin and only beginning investing my coin if the group was just missing its 4 people target. But there was no need for be to resort to investing my coin - the other participants were far too willing to each do this themselves! And then I got a bit greedy, I must admit.
Proper course of action for group dynamic is for all parties to invest in allshire and not keep the coin. Investing is long term hence stick with investing in allshire rather than keeping the coin.
I just decided to keep the coin on every round as I felt I would have the best chance of getting the most coins that way. I had no interest in what the others were doing or getting
HOPEFUL

I started off my investing as I thought it would give everybody a fair chance and then when more and more players were keeping the coins and I saw that I was losing out I chose to keep a few. In the end I probably kept more due to the fact that this is what the other players were doing
it was fun! hope i made a good bonus
N/A
Wanted to maximise the earnings for the group and ocasionally took the chance to increase my own earnings
I really enjoyed the study and the power of team work.
I tried to mix between keeping and making Allshire reach the target so that my actions were not predictable but made me the most bonus.
It was fun and interesting
It would of been easy if we all voted for Allshire and we would all get 2 coins each time but then you get  a couple of people who wanted the extra coin as well as the bonus 2 coins.
When i saw that not any people were investing in Allshire, i also stopped as I thought that we are less likely to reach the target.
felt like most were doing it for the good of the group

I initially chose to invest in Allshire every time, but occasionally as not everyone was, I chose to keep the coin, but on the whole, I'd rather invest in Allshire and get 2 coins, thank keep the coin and get 1.
I wasn't clear what the relevance of my being from Westville rather than Eastburgh was.
I went in wanting to be collaborative but as other people weren't cooperating, i changed to looking after my own best interests

Well I thought if we all just kept putting it in to the group we would all benefit so it seemed like a win win. But I guess some people just got greedy and wanted to get three coins, which meant that we started not reaching the target. I then decided just to keep a coin at the end because it seemed like nobody was working as a team.
I wanted everybody to get the most so I just invested in Allshire each time.
I just picked what I thought was best
I felt tempted to keep the coin on one round, but kept thinking that as on some other rounds two other players had opted to do this Had better not as then I would have ended up worse off.
best for each individual player was best for group
I waited for the group to go above the line before selecting a single coin instead of the group
I started off doing alternatively choosing the options, but found I was only getting 1 coin sometimes, then I stuck mainly with invest as most were doing that and it seemed almost a guarenteed win.
i felt a bit sad that some people were only looking out for themselves but also surprised that generally enough people invested to get to Target.

My strategy was to ensure the entire group did well. But as it went on and there was always 1 or 2 people maximising coin (never the full 6 helping all), I got a bit frustrated and decided to prioritise myself for a few rounds too.
It felt good to continue investing - I felt virtuous!
i just wanted to get as many as possible and not risk getting 0 in any round

I felt wrong when I chose to keep the coin. I often chose to invest when I felt that we wouldn't meet our target because I hoped that it would encourage others to do the same so that we could all win.

I would choose to keep the coin every few options so to earn a bit more because one person was doing it the entire time and obviously earned more than anyone else whilst being selfish to themselves I feel
Interesting game and makes me reflect on us as a society

i don't think the other players were real.   I started off thinking they might be and that sharing the coins were the best option but every round there were enough people who shared so it was better for me to choose the option not to share.and i concluded the other players did not exist
This was a great game, it was a great feeling when all players invested in Allshire for the 1st 3-4 rounds, i wont lie that I was very dissapointed when one of the players kept the coin.
I kept investing in Allshire because I reasoned we'd be more rich if we all invested in Allshire than if we all choose to keep the coin.
none

i started off trying to ensure we all got 2 coins each but people where keeping their coins and not investing which was leaving me with no coins so i then started keeping the coin myself to ensure i got at least 1 coin and sometimes 3
I felt that the best strategy for this game was to continue to invest in Allshare as I felt that had the best outcome for everyone.
i enjoyed this game

at the start I had every intention to pick invest in every round to help maximise everyone's bonus, but soon realised a couple of people were only out to maximise their own to 3 points, so in part to that theory and to test if I was playing with real people or not I chose not to invest for a couple of rounds to see what the outcome would be. I concluded they likely were real. I continued to be conflicted for the rest of the rounds, both investing and keeping hoping others would invest in some rounds, but found most often wouldn't when I did. So ended up not investing as much as I would have like to.
i wanted to invest in allshire and was glad when most people wanted that too
I wanted to invest everytime as I would feel bad if I kept the coin for myself.
I predominately focused on choosing the option that was most beneficial to the team, however I also aimed to maximise my own earnings on a few of the rounds.
A very good enjoyable game,. A good interesting study and very well presented.
I felt that if I were to start taking coins for myself everyone else will start doing it too.
if everyone earned 2 coins by hitting the target then everyone will do good. Some may keep a coin and benefit from the majority.
it is about contributing to the greater good and maximising income for all

i wanted to mostly select all share to maximise the potential coins for everyone. i noticed that there was a majority sharing so I occasionally clicked to keep extra coins myself mainly because 1 or more other players selected to do the same every so often
I was checking what the others would do at the beginning to see if i could use that to my advantage and get a couple more coins here and there
Throughout the game I chose to invest in Allshire, both so that I could get more coins and also so that others could gain as well.  I considered my advantage the same as everyone else's advantage.
i just clicked keep most the time
I felt like i wanted to switch up my earnings and the groups earnings

I might have got this wrong but as I don't think I was able to see what action each player took it was very hard to say how close I felt towards each group. I also wanted to go with the group each time but it was hard when the majority did not. At times it also felt like I was not actually playing with other people.

I figured everyone else would soon work out that the more of us click to invest in Allshire, the more likely we were to meet our target as a group. I didn't care that the people who voted to keep the coin would also get the bonus if we met the target; I just wanted to maximise my own winnings and if the others get more money too, that's good too! Plus it motivates them to have the same strategy as me, so we are all helping each other.
would have liked all to have invested but when understood that it was not likely, I switched to gain a small amount.
I stuck with saving my coins, hoping that it would force the other players to invest.

i felt guilty keeping the coin for myself

i was trying to maximise my winnings but would sometimes put add to pot to encourage others to do the same
i always voted to try and get the most points for the whole group
I THOUGHT THAT IT WAS EASIER TO ALWAYS INVEST IN THE ALLSHIRE
I was trying to get the most coins for myself. I tried to judge if, as a collective, at least 4 people would invest while I still kept my coin.
i was loooking for an uptik in the graphs
ensuring the threshold was met prior to my own needs.
I was trying to see if there was a consistent pattern of investment to allow me to drop out of some rounds but I mainly invested to ensure we met the 4 coin threshold
it was interesting to see what other participants voted for.

At first i wanted to see whether the group would meet the threshold and contributed to this.  Then there was a period early in the game when it seemed that the group was going to fail to do so, so I switched tack to keeping the coin.  However, the group regained the threshold and at the same time it became clear that my action was not crucial to meeting it.  Therefore, in order to maximize my own returns I kept the coin in addition to receiving the bonuses.

I thought others would also realise that by contributing to Allshire everyone would benefit so I kept putting my coins to Allshire in the hope others would too

just tried to be fair and get the best for everybody
As time went on, I thought I could get 3 coins each time so tactically invested to keep people investing in Allshire whilst I kept.
As in society, I felt that ensuring everyone got the best possible outcomes was, probably, the best way to proceed and acted upon it.
There was no benefit for Allshire for more than 4 people to invest. So if I assumed that there would be at least 4 people investing then i'd keep mine.
It was more important for me that everyone reach the goal than getting bogged down in what other people were doing, even when they were working against the group.

I wanted to firstly gauge if everyone was going to invest. Then I tried to keep my coin when I could see that 1 person was consistently keeping theirs. But ultimately it felt better and more straightforward to be investing in Allshire to keep the numbers up. I did feel slightly resentful towards those who were keeping their coins but also netting the +2 from the group's investment.
just trying to estimate when was not going to meet target to keep the coin

Being able to communicate with everyone else would mean that we could achieve a fairer outcome. I think that should always be part of studies like this because whatever findings you gain from this study it will be skewed by the fact that in real life people have the option to communicate.
I chose option 'keep the coin' as this did not affect the others in the group as there were always four people not choosing this option.
n/a
Strategy adjusted midway, to help maximise my own coins for my own reason(s), once it was clear that most players together, for +2 to everyone. Overall a very interesting study, thank you!
I enjoyed the game.

I was planning on keeping some coins to myself for some rounds but then I noticed after the first few rounds that everyone was choosing Allshire, so I decided to keep choosing Allshire as well because I didn't want to be the one to break the "streak".
Just making sure the target was met.

I tried to gain as many coins as possible by keeping my coin provided that enough invested to get the +2 coins back.  When more players stopped investing, I began to invest my coin to ensure returns. I felt that there would always be 4 players investing by combining the two areas and I was able to take a chance to get more coins which I suppose others could do too but I did not want to take a lot of chances where I might lose a coin

I would potentially have 'tried out' keeping the coin once or twice, just to get that extra 1 point, but there seemed to be always one person (whether it was the same person the whole time or not, I don't know) and sometimes another who kept the coin. I just felt that all players worked together to get the best result for al linvolved. The name Allshire also reminded me of "all share" so made me want us all to share in the best results.
I felt everyone would be willing to invest to win more, I went with a simple logical rule.

it was great

Interesting game once I understood the instructions.

At the start I was playing for the group then noticed everyone else was playing for themselves

I felt a bit devious during the game as I was trying to gain a little extra for myself without damaging the whole team.
it was fun

my strategy was to aim for the best bonus while following the safest technique

it is strategic

i was trying to think the way others might think.
It was frustrating as if we all worked together I think we would have got more but it was interesting
tried to be fair and good to have the chart and i think we done well as a team

I was being selfish with wanting to keep the coins for myself, as I thought this is the same for other players. I did sometimes invest the coin in the wider group community Allshire.
I waited until everyone was happy with four others voting for allshire, then I decided to be selfish

n/a
The game was a great one and i really enjoyed it

Was selfishly hoping that everyone else would get 2 coins, but I would click on 'keep coin' to get 3 each time.
I varied between keeping and investing the coin to ensure everyone was a winner in every round but also to maximise my winnings in some rounds

There was usually somone selfish who was keeping their coin but i took this on the chin as overall the team was still benefitting. However if there was a couple of rounds where less than 4 were investing i would also have changed my rersponse to investing and also kept the coins.
it is awsome

Tried a mix of investing and keeping. Hoped others would do the same and we all got a few 3s

After a couple of rounds of everyone agreeing to share, I figured 1 or 2 people could get a few extra coins and I wanted 1 of them to be me. Of course, anonymity helps a great deal. I doubt I would do the same otherwise.

I was hoping everyone else would invest in order to double our winnings, but it soon became clear that I was the only one investing so it was no point from that point on so I just had to keep the coin in order to at least get some money. I dont feel other people understood the game properly as they could have easily doubled their money by investing, but for some reason chose not to!
Felt interested in the metrics revealed on the page. Answered the question based on trends.

I was annoyed - if everyone gave to Allshire, everyone would benefit. People were too stupid to realise this. I gave everyone 3 chances to donate at the beginning, and when I realised everyone was looking out for themself, I gave up and kept the coin for myself as it was pointless donating.
This was a really interesting experiment to take part in. Thank you.
people were selfish
when the rest of the group invested in allshire i kept my coin in the following round in the hope that the rest of the group would continue to invest
Strategy was to see if allshire would meet the target without me often. If it would then I would chance it by keeping my coin sometimes.
strategy was to always give myself the coin as it was the lowest risk highest reward outcome. Best case scenario If everyone else invests I get 3 coins and if we dont meet the target I still get one.
i tried to be a good team (overall - allshire) team player
